{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow childminders to access government funding for care of related children",
        "additional_details": "Childminders are not currently permitted to receive funding under the Government\u2019s 15 or 30 hours childcare entitlements for childcare they provide to the children of family members. Changing this would help families pay for childcare and give the children the best care. During the pandemic, many children could have been supported by someone who yes is their grandparent but who is also a childcare professional.",
        "background": "Ofsted-registered childminders in England should be able to draw down government funding for providing care for their own grandchildren and other related children. In Wales this is already in place.",
